[[File:Charlotte Blease.jpg|thumb|Image of Dr Charlotte Blease giving a keynote address at Inspirefest 2016. This picture was taken by Conor McCabe Photography]] '''Charlotte Blease''' is a Northern Irish science philosopher and cognitive scientist from [[Belfast]], [[Northern Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siliconrepublic.com/innovation/women-scientists-global-research-science |title=20 incredible women leading the way to scientific advancement |publisher=Siliconrepublic.com |date= |accessdate=2017-11-22}}</ref> She is an [[Irish Research Council]] fellow and a [[University College Dublin]] lecturer.
== History == Blease studied philosophy and the philosophy of science at [[Queen's University, Belfast]].<ref name=ac>{{cite web|author= |url=https://ucd.academia.edu/CharlotteBlease |title=Charlotte Blease - University College Dublin |publisher=Academia.edu |date= |accessdate=2017-11-22}}</ref> Afterwards she attended [[Harvard University]] in the United States.<ref name=ac /> Following this, Blease wrote a number of published academic papers on the issue of psychology and philosophy of science utilizing different schools of thought combined.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siliconrepublic.com/innovation/charlotte-blease-irish-research-council-heroes |title=The need for cosmopolitan ideals in research – Dr Charlotte Blease |publisher=Siliconrepublic.com |date= |accessdate=2017-11-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://scholar.google.co.uk/citations?user=KL5fMn0AAAAJ&hl=en |title=Charlotte Blease |publisher=Google Scholar Citations |date= |accessdate=2017-11-22}}</ref> She then started teaching at University College Dublin in the Republic of Ireland, specialising in research into placebos as a research fellow after a grant from the Irish Research Council.<ref name=ac /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smh.com.au/national/health/mindbody-healing-success-of-placebo-trials-challenges-medical-thinking-20170605-gwkk2c.html |title='Mind-body' healing: Success of placebo trials challenges medical thinking |publisher=Sydney Morning Herald |date=2017-06-11 |accessdate=2017-11-22}}</ref> Blease also held the position of postdoctoral research fellow at the English [[University of Leeds]] and worked as a placebo research affiliate at [[Harvard Medical School]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mh.bmj.com/content/42/3/200 |title=Scholar spotlight on Dr Charlotte Blease and Prof Allan Peterkin |publisher=British Medical Journal |date=2016-08-24 |accessdate=2017-11-22}}</ref>
Blease has been an advocate for the teaching of philosophy in schools<ref>{{cite web|author=Joe Humphreys |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/education/sabina-higgins-backs-campaign-for-teaching-philosophy-in-schools-1.2770953 |title=Sabina Higgins backs campaign for teaching philosophy in schools |publisher=Irish Times |date=2016-08-28 |accessdate=2017-11-22}}</ref> and wrote in the British newspaper ''[[The Guardian]]'' supporting this.<ref>{{cite web|first=Charlotte |last=Blease |url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2017/jan/09/philosophy-teach-children-schools-ireland |title=Philosophy can teach children what Google can't – and Ireland knows it |publisher=The Guardian |date= |accessdate=2017-11-22}}</ref>
